\section{Performance in the Single-User Scenario}
\label{sect:single-user}
For the mixed-ADC architecture, since there is no closed-form expression for the capacity, in this paper, we leverage GMI to evaluate its achievable data rates. GMI characterizes the achievable data rate of specific codebook ensemble (Gaussian ensemble here) and specific decoding rule (generalized nearest-neighbor decoding here), and usually leads to manageable analytical results. As a performance metric, it has proven convenient and useful in several important scenarios, such as fading channel with imperfect CSI at the receiver \cite{lapidoth2002fading} and channels with transceiver distortion \cite{liang2015mixed}-\cite{liang2015a}, \cite{zhang2012general}-\cite{vehkapera2015asymptotic}.

