\subsection{Extension to Ergodic Time-Varying Channels}
\label{subsect:ergodic_single}
Applying a similar argument as \cite[Prop. 4]{liang2015mixed}, we extend the analytical results in Section III-A to ergodic time-varying channels and obtain lower and upper bounds of the GMI. Numerical results will be given in Section \ref{sect:numerical} to confirm the tightness of the bounds.
\begin{prop}
For ergodic time-varying SIMO-OFDM channels, the lower and upper bounds of $I_{\mathrm{GMI}}$ follow from
\begin{eqnarray}
I_{\mathrm{GMI}}^{\mathrm{lower}}&=&\log\left(1+\frac{\mathbb{E}_{\mathbf{h}_n,n\in\mathbb{N}}[\Delta(\mathbf{w}_{\mathrm{opt}},\bm{\delta})]}{1-\mathbb{E}_{\mathbf{h}_n,n\in\mathbb{N}}[\Delta(\mathbf{w}_{\mathrm{opt}},\bm{\delta})]}\right),\\
I_{\mathrm{GMI}}^{\mathrm{upper}}&=&\mathbb{E}_{\mathbf{h}_n,n\in\mathbb{N}}\left[\log\left(1+\frac{\Delta(\mathbf{w}_{\mathrm{opt}},\bm{\delta})}{1-\Delta(\mathbf{w}_{\mathrm{opt}},\bm{\delta})}\right)\right],
\end{eqnarray}
respectively. Here $\Delta(\mathbf{w}_{\mathrm{opt}},\bm{\delta})$ is also given by \eqref{equ:prop_1.2}, for each sample of the ergodic time-varying channel.
\end{prop}

\section{Multi-user scenario}
\label{sect:multi-user}
\subsection{System Description}
A total of $U$ users communicate to the BS simultaneously. Again we start by focusing on the static channels with perfect CSI at the BS. The $u$-th user's OFDM symbol is $\mathcal{CN}(\mathbf{0},\mathcal{E}_{\mathrm{s}}\mathbf{I}_Q)$ distributed and is denoted by $\tilde{\mathbf{x}}^u$. Before transmission, an IDFT is applied to $\tilde{\mathbf{x}}^u$ and the actual transmit symbol of user $u$ is $\mathbf{x}^u=\mathbf{F}^{\dag}\tilde{\mathbf{x}}^u$, which is also $\mathcal{CN}(\mathbf{0},\mathcal{E}_{\mathrm{s}}\mathbf{I}_Q)$ distributed. We further assume that the OFDM symbols from different users are independently distributed, since typically the users do not cooperate with each other.

